description:
Modify `apps/task-manager/src/types/execution.ts` to add TypeScript types for team activity data.

**Existing Types to Extend:**
- `ExecutionProgress` — add optional team summary fields
- `ExecutionContext` — type already handles artifacts generically, but structured team data needs types

**New Types to Add:**

```typescript
interface TeamMember {
  role: 'explorer' | 'implementer' | 'reviewer';
  name: string;
  status: 'waiting' | 'active' | 'completed' | 'failed';
  currentPhase: string;
}

interface TeamActivityLogEntry {
  timestamp: string;
  role: string;
  event: string;
}

interface TeamActivity {
  taskId: string;
  teamName: string;
  strategy: 'solo' | 'review' | 'research' | 'full';
  status: 'active' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'degraded';
  created: string;
  updated: string;
  members: TeamMember[];
  activityLog: TeamActivityLogEntry[];
}
```

**Extensions to ExecutionProgress:**
```typescript
// Add to existing ExecutionProgress interface:
activeTeams?: Array<{
  taskId: string;
  teamName: string;
  strategy: string;
  memberCount: number;
  status: string;
}>;
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**

_Functional:_
- [ ] TeamMember type with role, name, status, currentPhase fields
- [ ] TeamActivity type with all fields matching file format
- [ ] TeamActivityLogEntry type for activity log entries
- [ ] ExecutionProgress extended with optional activeTeams array
- [ ] All types exported from execution.ts

_Edge Cases:_
- [ ] All team-related fields are optional (backwards compatible with non-team sessions)
- [ ] Strategy type union includes all 4 strategy values

_Error Handling:_
- [ ] Status fields use union types for type safety

**Testing Requirements:**
- Unit: TypeScript compilation passes with new types
- Manual: Verify types match the team_activity.md file format specification

Source: internal/specs/agent-teams-updates-SPEC.md Section 5.7
